<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="482" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Tri-Motors Safety
                                Airways/97: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-17T15:00:00-04:00">August 17, 1929—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>46. If the Brazilian Government inquires you may say for the
                                information of the Minister of Transportation that the Department is
                                informed that the New York, Rio and Buenos Aires Line, Incorporated,
                                is American owned and financed solely by American money and that
                                Trimotors Safety Airways, Incorporated, is a subsidiary of the New
                                York, Rio and Buenos Aires Line entirely owned by it and with no
                                foreign interest or control.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>